claim.claim-text:
7. A method for monitoring an efficiency of an exhaust gas aftertreatment device disposed in an exhaust passage of an internal combustion engine, the device having a sensor coupled downstream of it, the method comprising: 
providing an indication of low space velocity; 
in response to said indication, operating the engine at an air-fuel ratio lean of stoichiometry thereby causing an exhaust gas component to be stored in the device; 
switching engine operation to an air-fuel ratio rich of stoichiometry based on an output of the sensor thereby releasing said stored exhaust gas component from the device; and 
calculating an amount of fuel required to complete said release.
